Instructions for Arduino IDE Setup (ESP32-S3 + OV2640 Camera)

Please make sure to follow these steps in Arduino IDE to upload and run the example correctly:

1. Install ESP32 Board Support

Open Arduino IDE → File → Preferences → in "Additional Board Manager URLs" add:

https://dl.espressif.com/dl/package_esp32_index.json

Then go to Tools → Board → Boards Manager and install "esp32 by Espressif Systems" (latest version).



2. Select the Correct Board Settings

Board: ESP32S3 Dev Module

USB CDC On Boot: Enabled

Flash Mode: QIO

Flash Size: (depending on the module, usually 8MB or 16MB)

PSRAM: Enabled

Partition Scheme: Huge APP (3MB No OTA/1MB SPIFFS)

Upload Speed: 921600

Programmer: USB-CDC (UART0)



3. Library

Include the ESP32 Camera library (already comes with the ESP32 board package).

Example can be found under: File → Examples → ESP32 → Camera → CameraWebServer.



4. WiFi Credentials

In the sketch, update:

const char* ssid = "YOUR_WIFI_SSID";
const char* password = "YOUR_WIFI_PASSWORD";



5. Upload & Run

Connect the ESP32-S3 board via USB-C.

Select the correct COM port.

Upload the code.

Open Serial Monitor (115200 baud).

After connection, it will print the IP address. Open that in a browser to see the camera stream.

	
